Czech Stocks Decline First Day in Three, Led by CEZ, New World

-- B y   K r y s t o f   C h a m o n i k o l a s
-- 
2011-02-15T09:42:11Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-15/czech-stocks-decline-first-day-in-three-led-by-cez-new-world.html
The Czech Republic’s benchmark stock
index snapped a two-day rally, led down by  CEZ AS , the country’s
biggest power utility, and coal company  New World Resources NV .  The PX gauge of 15 companies slid 0.5 percent to 1,245 by
10:05 a.m. in Prague after gaining 1.3 percent in the previous
two sessions. CEZ slumped 1.6 percent to 803 koruna, its lowest
in more than a month, and NWR lost 1.3 percent to 280 koruna.  CEZ and NWR have a combined 31 percent weighting in the PX.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Krystof Chamonikolas in Prague at 
 kchamonikola@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gavin Serkin at   gserkin@bloomberg.net  